
1. JS
 - load scripts from node_modules
 - load custom scripts from resource folder
 - have custom scripts for each page like index.js, products.js, etc.
 - load modules with requirejs or browserifyjs in these custom scripts
 - end point js to be minified if env is production
 - custom js outside node_modules to go through jshint/jslint
 - generate sourcemaps

 https://www.viget.com/articles/gulp-browserify-starter-faq
 https://github.com/gulpjs/gulp/blob/master/docs/recipes/browserify-transforms.md
 https://wehavefaces.net/gulp-browserify-the-gulp-y-way-bb359b3f9623#.44yrfu8xl
 https://lincolnloop.com/blog/untangle-your-javascript-browserify/
 http://fettblog.eu/gulp-browserify-multiple-bundles/
 https://justinjohnson.org/javascript/getting-started-with-gulp-and-browserify/
 http://www.sitepoint.com/getting-started-browserify/

2. CSS
 - compile custom sass
 - concat custom css
 - load css from node_modules
 - end point css to be minified if env is production
 - make sourcemaps
 - output errors in console